01:08:27,845 --> 01:08:43,371
Dear Mr. President, city councilors, I respectfully request and recommend that your Honorable body approves the appropriation of retained earnings in the amount of $268,000.00 to fund repairs to Douglas Road due to a leak in the water main line causing flooding.

869
01:08:43,931 --> 01:08:46,352
The balance of retained earnings before this vote is $7,389,422.00.

870
01:08:46,412 --> 01:08:52,195
DDBW Commissioner Brian Kerins is present to answer any questions for the council regarding this matter.

871
01:08:58,108 --> 01:09:00,049
Mr. Kearns, name and address for the record, please.

872
01:09:00,870 --> 01:09:03,492
Brian Kearns, Milton Terrace Hyde Park.

873
01:09:04,753 --> 01:09:06,474
Do we have any questions for Mr. Kearns?

874
01:09:06,935 --> 01:09:07,675
Councillor Falco.

875
01:09:08,035 --> 01:09:08,956
Thank you, Mr. President.

876
01:09:08,976 --> 01:09:10,517
Mr. Kearns, just a couple of quick questions.

877
01:09:10,557 --> 01:09:14,920
Can you just tell us a little bit about the water leak, the cause of the water leak, when it happens?

878
01:09:16,178 --> 01:09:24,943
It was brought to my attention by a constituent a little over a month ago that he was getting water in his basement.

879
01:09:25,823 --> 01:09:33,668
At that point in time, I had our water and sewer department dispatched out there to see where the source was potentially coming from.

880
01:09:34,848 --> 01:09:42,872
And the long and short of it is we narrowed it down to the actual main itself on the street.

881
01:09:44,412 --> 01:09:47,334
And we had our own leak detection equipment out there.

882
01:09:47,934 --> 01:09:52,216
We also called in MWRA to come in and assist us.

883
01:09:52,316 --> 01:09:53,877
They have a more elaborate setup.

884
01:09:54,617 --> 01:10:00,500
Off peak time, daytime, nighttime, to try to narrow down exactly where this leak was occurring.

885
01:10:01,240 --> 01:10:14,549
All right, and we've actually isolated it down to a 400-foot section of main that the leak is in, but we can't narrow it down any further than that because that whole area is impacted with clay.

886
01:10:15,149 --> 01:10:22,154
Clay is actually acting as an insulation around the existing pipe that's there, and we're losing the sound.

887
01:10:22,194 --> 01:10:25,456
It's almost like sonar gear for a submarine, all right?

888
01:10:25,936 --> 01:10:27,698
We can hear it, but then it stops.

889
01:10:28,378 --> 01:10:38,080
Now, we've shut off the actual main itself, all right, in both directions, and when we do that, the leak in the home stops, okay?

890
01:10:38,380 --> 01:10:45,762
So, as a result of that, we know that there is a leak that has occurred and is occurring within this 400-foot section.

891
01:10:46,342 --> 01:10:52,744
Now, going back through the history, all right, obviously, this is Douglas Road, by the way, between Summer and George, all right?

892
01:10:53,324 --> 01:10:56,665
The water main that exists today was installed in 1927.

893
01:10:58,585 --> 01:11:16,106
It's a six inch main and given the age factor with tuberculation has occurred, there's probably maybe only a three inch clearance going through the existing pipe as it stands today, which is not uncommon in the water and sewer business.

894
01:11:18,849 --> 01:11:23,714
The main service is 32 homes on that street.

895
01:11:25,056 --> 01:11:33,684
Going through all the records and everything, it was just several years ago, the gas main was replaced on that entire street.

896
01:11:35,186 --> 01:11:50,137
Well, as a result of the age and the condition of this pipe, the amount of pipe that we already have to replace, meeting with the mayor, we both agreed to replace the entire main on the street.

897
01:11:51,777 --> 01:12:02,242
And to do it right away because even if we just replace that 400 foot section, through my experience in this business, once you touch something, it spreads.

898
01:12:03,522 --> 01:12:06,963
And let's do it one stop shopping here.

899
01:12:07,284 --> 01:12:09,244
Replace the entire main right away.

900
01:12:10,505 --> 01:12:17,948
We already have a contractor in the city who's actually working down on, I think it's one of the side streets down there.

901
01:12:18,568 --> 01:12:22,550
I can have them start as early as next week to put the new main in.

902
01:12:23,070 --> 01:12:27,852
Now, we put a winter binder on the main once it's installed.

903
01:12:29,072 --> 01:12:40,217
Then return in the spring because with the money that the DPW has requested, $268,000, that's also going to do curb-to-curb repaving in the spring.

904
01:12:41,277 --> 01:12:50,465
some casting adjustments and some new castings as needed, curbing adjustments as needed, and sidewalk replacement panels as needed.

905
01:12:50,505 --> 01:12:57,951
All right, we're gonna go full, full width down the entire length of that street, and that will, you know, to completely upgrade the street.

906
01:12:59,392 --> 01:13:09,961
Actually, in addition to that, we're probably also gonna install an additional fire hydrant, okay, even though there's adequate fire suppression there, an additional one while we're installing, okay, the new main.

907
01:13:11,162 --> 01:13:14,247
It sounds like there's two parts to the project.

908
01:13:14,287 --> 01:13:19,334
As far as replacing the main, putting in the new hydrant, how long will that take?

909
01:13:20,227 --> 01:13:34,678
The new main, if he were to get the green light from the council this evening, he probably would be starting maybe actually a week from today, all right, or next Wednesday he'd start, and he could probably go within a couple of weeks.

910
01:13:35,058 --> 01:13:39,462
Again, with weather, you know, that would also have to be the concern as well.

911
01:13:40,602 --> 01:13:44,465
But, you know, we want to, you know, go right ahead and do it right away.

912
01:13:44,946 --> 01:13:47,708
And, you know, within two weeks he'd have the new main in.

913
01:13:48,743 --> 01:13:59,225
So when they're actually installing the new main, what can the residents expect as far as will they be without water periods during the day, I imagine?

914
01:13:59,265 --> 01:14:10,907
No, there'd be no loss of water service council because what we would do is we would install a temporary line that would be on the surface of the roadway in the gutter line going to the individual homes.

915
01:14:11,607 --> 01:14:16,908
And then at that point, we shut the main down and then excavate and start replacing it.

916
01:14:18,109 --> 01:14:24,153
So I actually took a ride down the street the other day just to kind of check out the situation and view it firsthand.

917
01:14:24,713 --> 01:14:27,495
