919
01:14:31,978 --> 01:14:34,020
It looks like something's going on underneath.

920
01:14:34,780 --> 01:14:36,141
Yeah, it's the soil.

921
01:14:36,441 --> 01:14:43,365
Like I said, it's heavily loaded with clay in that area.

922
01:14:43,425 --> 01:14:48,608
It's probably one of the worst types of soil you want to deal with.

923
01:14:48,668 --> 01:14:56,373
When we come back in in the spring and we scarify and do repaving, we'd be eliminating it at that point in time.

924
01:14:56,893 --> 01:15:03,437
Is there any concern, so when you connect that main on Douglas, that's connecting then to?

925
01:15:03,897 --> 01:15:04,958
Yeah, it's Summer and George.

926
01:15:05,338 --> 01:15:06,219
Summer and George, okay.

927
01:15:06,599 --> 01:15:08,400
Okay, and they're okay.

928
01:15:08,420 --> 01:15:09,160
Those are newer mains?

929
01:15:09,260 --> 01:15:11,101
Right, yeah, no problems there.

930
01:15:11,362 --> 01:15:18,186
But this will also include new T's, valves, shutoffs, be the full gamut on that street.

931
01:15:19,406 --> 01:15:25,051
We can take advantage of it because, like I said, it was only several years ago the new gas main was installed there.

932
01:15:25,331 --> 01:15:30,575
So I'm not concerned with the utility companies coming in for an emergency at any point in time in the near future.

933
01:15:31,805 --> 01:15:37,848
I mean, it sounds like, I mean, it's almost 100 years old, so it sounds like the whole thing probably should be replaced, but thank you very much.

934
01:15:37,908 --> 01:15:38,708
